events.name: Denver Broncos at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: — Patrick Mahomes knows the Kansas City Chiefs' offense is still trying to put everything together.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes throws TD pass, Kelce has big game with Swift watching again as Chiefs beat Broncos 19-8

headlines.description: — Lamar Jackson scrambled, evaded tackles and made big throws when he needed to in his international debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson throws TD pass and Tucker kicks 6 FGs for Ravens in 24-16 win over Titans in London

headlines.description: — Jamin Davis sensed where the final pass was going before it left the quarterback's hand.
headlines.shortLinkText: Howell throws 3 TD passes, Commanders pick off three Ridder passes in 24-16 win over Falcons

headlines.description: — The Minnesota Vikings took a cue from the Texas Rangers and decided to play a Creed song. They chose “Higher” and sent Chicago toward another low.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cousins, Hicks lead way as Vikings knock out Fields, beat Bears 19-13

headlines.description: — When Joe Burrow couldn't get the ball in the end zone in the second half Sunday, the Cincinnati defense made sure the Seattle Seahawks didn't either.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bengals defense shuts down Seattle twice late to seal a 17-13 win and improve to 3-3

headlines.description: — From dominant to defeated — in less than a week. The San Francisco 49ers were reminded there are no perfect teams or givens in the NFL.
headlines.shortLinkText: Browns stun 49ers 19-17, hand San Francisco its first loss and QB Brock Purdy his first as starter

headlines.description: — Tyreek Hill knows he has a fine coming for his touchdown celebration in Sunday's 42-21 win over the Carolina Panthers. The NFL’s leading receiver — who caught one of Tua Tagovailoa's three TD passes — said it was worth it.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tua Tagovailoa throws 3 TD passes to rally the Dolphins past the Panthers 42-21

headlines.description: — Trevor Lawrence walked through the locker room and to the postgame podium without a limp or anything on his injured left knee.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaguars beat Minshew and the Colts 37-20 for their 9th consecutive home victory in the series

events.name: New Orleans Saints at Houston Texans

headlines.description: — After failing to get a late stop in a loss to the Falcons last week, the Houston Texans got two in the last five minutes on Sunday to secure a victory over the New Orleans Saints.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stroud throws 2 TD passes, defense makes late stops to lead Texans over Saints 20-13

events.name: New England Patriots at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: — Hanging over a game in which several ex-New England Patriots played key roles in a victory against their former team was the loss of Las Vegas Raiders quarterback Jimmy Garoppolo to a back injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raiders hold off Patriots 21-17 after losing QB Garoppolo to back injury

events.name: Arizona Cardinals at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: — Although the Los Angeles Rams have played plenty of stellar offensive football over the past seven seasons, Sean McVay's team hasn't usually done it by simply squaring its shoulders and running the ball straight through opposing defenses.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cooper Kupp, Kyren Williams score 2nd-half touchdowns in Rams' 26-9 win over Cardinals

events.name: Philadelphia Eagles at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Robert Saleh stepped from the podium at his postgame news conference and let loose a little.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hall runs for a TD after Adams' INT and Jets shock Eagles 20-14 to send Philly to its first loss

events.name: Detroit Lions at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: — Jared Goff and the streaking Detroit Lions keep finding different ways to win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Goff throws for 353 yards, 2 TDs to lead NFC North-leading Lions past sputtering Buccaneers 20-6

events.name: New York Giants at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: — It took Josh Allen and the Buffalo Bills offense nearly three quarters to find their rhythm.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buffalo Bills hang on -- barely -- in a 14-9 win over the New York Giants

events.name: Dallas Cowboys at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: — Fans and some players might roll their eyes when a Week 6 game is described as a must win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dak Prescott, Cowboys rally in fourth quarter for a 20-17 victory over the Chargers
